## Build

```sh
rustup target add wasm32-unknown-unknown
cargo build --release --target wasm32-unknown-unknown
# Output: target/wasm32-unknown-unknown/release/{{.CrateName}}.wasm
```

Copy the artefact next to `plugin.yaml` so the signer + the install
pipeline find it:

```sh
cp target/wasm32-unknown-unknown/release/{{.CrateName}}.wasm {{.EntryWasm}}
```

## Sign

```sh
# One-time keygen (skip if you already have a publisher keypair):
platypus-cli plugin keygen \
    --out-secret ~/.platypus/publisher.secret \
    --out-public ~/.platypus/publisher.pub

# Sign this plugin:
platypus-cli plugin sign \
    --key ~/.platypus/publisher.secret \
    --wasm {{.EntryWasm}}
# Produces {{.EntryWasm}}.minisig.
```

Then update `plugin.yaml` so `signature.key_id` matches your
publisher key id (printed by `keygen`).

## Validate

```sh
platypus-cli plugin validate-manifest plugin.yaml
```

## Install

Drop the public key on every agent that should accept plugins
signed by you:

```sh
cp ~/.platypus/publisher.pub \
    /etc/platypus/agent/plugins/publishers/<key-id>.pub
```

For dev / system-managed plugins, stage the bundle under the server's
system-plugins directory and the agent picks it up on next reconcile.
For marketplace-distributed plugins, publish to your index.
